    <fr:title text="Affine scheme at a stalk">Affine scheme at a stalk</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">scheme</fr:link> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}{\mathcal {O}_{X,x}}]]></fr:tex> as a topological space is the subspace <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\uparrow  x]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. Furthermore, this gives us a map
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \operatorname {Spec}{\mathcal {O}_{X,x}} \to  X. ]]></fr:tex></html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>11</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> be an affine open of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> as a prime filter of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> (cf. <fr:link href="/schm-B6QO/" title="Stalk for structural sheaf" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-B6QO/" display-uri="schm-B6QO" type="local">Remark <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-B6QO/" display-uri="schm-B6QO" /></fr:link>),
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \mathcal {O}_{X,x} \cong  A/x. ]]></fr:tex>
  This way, the quotient <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A \twoheadrightarrow  A/x]]></fr:tex> induces the inclusion <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}{\mathcal {O}_{X,x}} \to  \operatorname {Spec} A \subseteq  X]]></fr:tex>. Verifying this does not depend on the specific choice of the affine open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> is routine.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
